<Author>edinburghedge
<Content>Average and Overpriced The Carolus Hotel is rated a four star property on Expedia but is actually, at most, an adequate three star hotel with four star prices. We took a bus from Pisa airport into Florence, 拢3, and the hotel is just a five minute cab ride, 拢6, from the bus station. (Buses are more reliable and more convenient than trains throughout Tuscany.) We could have walked to the hotel but the traffic is heavy and the sidewalks are narrow and very crowded. All the major museums and attractions are easily walkable from the hotel and there's a good range of shops and cafes nearby. We had a pleasant stay in room #208 for two nights, October 4 and 5. The room was large by European standards, clean and well presented. The bathroom was spacious, full sized bathtub, although the amenities were somewhat lacking in assortment. The towels were disappointingly thin and poor quality but the water pressure was strong and there was plenty of hot water at all times. The room was well air conditioned, and still needed in October, but we learned that not securely closing the bathroom window caused the A/C to shut off. We didn't use the mini-bar but we did take advantage of the extra space in the refrigertor to store our own water. The closet only had two hangers, I'm sure we could have asked for more but we simply made do. The two twin beds were small and the mattresses were very firm... perhaps a bit too firm. The view from the window, looking onto one of the smaller domes in the city, was lovely and the best aspect of this room. The buffet breakfast was rather plain: coffee, juices, cereal, various breads, cake, ham, cheeses and fruit. Cooked items are available at an extra cost but we didn't bother. We arrived at the hotel at noon and our room was available by 1:00pm. The reception staff, along with housekeeping and breakfast service were very good... friendly and professional. We liked this hotel well enough but nothing about it is 'four star'. I don't think we would consider staying here again. The hotel would benefit from some general maintenance, a fresh coat of paint on the walls would be a good start. The breakfast room and common areas are a depressing shade of pale blue and covered with spots, smudges and scuff marks... the entire property has a slightly neglected feel. Overall, at 拢125 per night, it wasn't good value for money and was our least favorite of the three hotels we visited in Tuscany. 
