<Content>Carolus was perfect Just returned from four night stay in Florence at Carolus Hotel. Quite simply one of the best hotels I have stayed at in over twenty years of travelling. Whilst areas like the corridors were not the tidiest (scuff marks from suitcases) the rooms and general public areas were spotless and very comfortable. We stayed on the third floor and had a view over towards Fiesole which was excellent. The air conditioning worked well and was very quiet, the showere was hot and with good pressure. The bed was comfortable and was truned down in the evenings after we had gone out for dinner which was a nice touch as we generally followed the Florentine example and had a short rest after lunch.Checking in and out of this hotel was simply the best I have ever experienced. The desk staff were well informed, I had specified that I wanted a room on an upper floor and had requested they reserve me museum tickets, all of which was done without any fuss. Check-in took about a minute and check-out about thirty seconds - just brilliant!The area around the hotel was quite quiet, mainly residential with a couple of bars and restaurants however there were plenty of eating and drinking opportunities within five minutes walk in either direction from the hotel door.I would definatley stay here again and reccoment anyone to do likewise. 
