<Author>Avid_Traveler
<Content>A Wonderful Stay Just returned from a 5 night stay at the Carolus Hotel. The service was top notch. We arrived at the hotel around 12:45pm (a bit early for check-in) and was greeted warmly. Although the room was not ready, we were escorted to a comfortable seating room and was offered a pot of coffee. Nice touch for us weary travelers. We had just flown in from NY through Rome and had just taken the Eurostar to Florence from the Termini station. Our room was ready in about 15 minutes. Was pleasantly surprised by the layout of the room (shaped like a U), with wood parquet floors, separate desk and writing area, and modern bathroom, with a towel warmer. Room was extremely clean, and elegantly furnished (not over the top). Conveniently located, within walking distance to the Academia (Il Centro supermarket located across from the Academia for basic essentials, i.e. water, soda, juice.) Beware the mosquitos though. Florence in general is notorious for mosquitoes year round. Windows, although shuttered, had no screens to keep those critters out. Don't leave them open overnight or they'll eat you alive. :) Breakfast buffet included in price. Nice selection of proscuitto, ham, cheeses, croissants, rolls, cereal, jams and Nutella (my favorite!!). Although it does get boring after 5 days. :) There are only so many ways one can eat proscuitto and cheese, and cheese and proscuitto. :) But the wait staff was wonderful and attentive. Good coffee as well.Thanks to the front desk and reception, who helped us out when we forgot our universal adaptor and lent us one for our stay. When we booked the Carolus, we relied on the positive comments from other tripadvisor users. Thanks for all your feedback and comments. 
