<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Second Time-Very Good Decision I got back to Hotel Carolus one year later and stayed five nights in August of 2004. I paid Euro 105 per day for a single room. To me it is a reasonable price by considering the hotel's quality.All staff has always a kind smile on their face. And they are very helpful when you need any information. In my opinion, housekeeping is also very good. My room was very clean as last year. Surprisingly enough, they make even a second turn in the evening when you are out and if necessary they change your towel etc. This year I grabbed a room with a good view; part of the city, roofs and the mountains.As in the last year, air conditioning in the room and in the lobby was very good. The service in the breakfast room is decent and the staff is very kind. To me breakfast was sufficient by especially considering my experience in some other four star hotels. This time I decided to give the name of some restaurants I liked.For a tasteful dinner, you can try one of these restaurants: Ristorante Ottorino (good service, good food, very near to Duomo - Tel:055.21.87.47), Tavernetta Della Signoria (small place, but superb food - Tel: 055.28.89.51), Ristorante I Quattro Amici (around 15 minutes walk from the center, especially fish - Tel: 055.21.54.13), Don Chisciotte (near to Carolus, especially fish, but unfortunately mostly closed in August - Tel:055.47.54.30).In summary, I suggest Hotel Carolus to all of my friends in my circle without any hesitation. And I hope to come back again. 
